## 🔐 EKEX Intelligence — Network Service Amendments

> **⚠️ CRITICAL:** These amendments apply to ALL deployments of EKEX Intelligence as a network service (SaaS, API, bot, or any remote user interaction).

### 📋 Amendment Index

| # | Amendment | Status |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Source Offer Mechanism | **MANDATORY** |
| 2 | Corresponding Source Definition | **MANDATORY** |
| 3 | No Proprietary Wrapper Circumvention | **MANDATORY** |
| 4 | White-Label & Multi-Tenant | **MANDATORY** |
| 5 | No Commercial Sublicensing | **MANDATORY** |
| 6 | Attribution | **MANDATORY** |
| 7 | Jurisdiction | **MANDATORY** |

---

### 1️⃣ Source Offer Mechanism

Any deployment of EKEX Intelligence that allows users to interact with the software remotely through a computer network **MUST** prominently provide a mechanism for all such users to obtain the **Corresponding Source** of the deployed version, including all modifications, configurations, and derivative works.

**✅ Acceptable Mechanisms:**

| Method | Implementation |
|---|---|
| UI Footer | `"Source"` link in user interface footer or navigation |
| API Endpoint | `GET /source` or `GET /license` returning source access info |
| Bot Message | NEZA bot (Telegram/WhatsApp) replies with source URL |
| Documentation | Prominently linked from all user-facing entry points |

---

### 2️⃣ Corresponding Source Definition

For EKEX Intelligence, `"Corresponding Source"` includes:

```
📦 Corresponding Source Package
├── 📁 src/                    All AGPL-3.0-licensed modules
├── 📁 neza/                   NEZA intent engine models & weights
├── 📁 inference/              AI inference layer code
├── 📁 ekex/                   EKEX intelligence infrastructure
├── 📁 api/                    REST/GraphQL endpoints
├── 📄 docker-compose.yml      Deployment manifests
├── 📄 Dockerfile              Container build scripts
├── 📄 .env.example            Configuration templates
└── 📄 docs/                   Public documentation
```

---

### 3️⃣ 🚫 No Proprietary Wrapper Circumvention

Deploying reverse proxies, CDNs, API gateways, or middleware that obscure, modify, or intercept EKEX API requests/responses **WITHOUT** offering Corresponding Source constitutes a **direct license violation**.

> Building a proprietary frontend, mobile app, or wrapper around EKEX APIs does **NOT** exempt you from source disclosure obligations for the underlying EKEX deployment.

---

### 4️⃣ White-Label & Multi-Tenant Deployments

White-label, reseller, or multi-tenant deployments **MUST** provide source access to **ALL** end users interacting with the software, not merely the deploying entity. Each end user's interface **MUST** contain the source offer mechanism.

---

### 5️⃣ 🚫 No Commercial Sublicensing

EKEX Intelligence is licensed under **AGPL-3.0 ONLY**. No contributor or deployer may grant proprietary sublicenses, commercial licenses, or closed-source distribution rights for any code derived from this repository.

**✅ Permitted Revenue Models:**

| Service | Description |
|---|---|
| Consulting | Architecture review, customization guidance |
| Support | Priority technical support, SLA guarantees |
| Hosting | Managed EKEX deployments |
| Deployment | Installation, configuration, migration |

**🚫 Prohibited:** Proprietary forks, closed-source modules, relicensing.

---

### 6️⃣ Attribution

All deployments **MUST** retain the following attribution in user-facing interfaces and API responses:

```
Powered by EKEX Intelligence — Open Intent Intelligence Infrastructure
https://EKEXintelligence.com · Licensed under GNU AGPLv3
```

---

### 7️⃣ ⚖️ Jurisdiction

| Aspect | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Governing Law** | Laws of Rwanda |
| **Dispute Resolution** | Binding arbitration at Kigali International Arbitration Centre (KIAC) |
| **Arbitration Seat** | Kigali, Rwanda |

